		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>extending 72 pin connector</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />has anyone successfully extended a 72 pin connector from the board to a external location for the cart tray?  I have tried using a shielded ribbon cable and cat5 to extend the 72 pin ~5'.  Both tries netted me nothing but a solid gray screen.  power light comes on solid, turns gray if I have a cart on the slot.  w/o cart power light just blinks and shows a black screen.  I have extended the controller ports w/ cat5 and the power wires w/ 18ga primary wire and both work fine.  At first I thought it was a resistance problem for the 72 pin and that is when I re-soldered everything w/ cat5.  Now I am thinking it may be voltage drop.  any ideas?  thanks in advance!
<br />
<br />-adam

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


